Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: Indict and remand
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00ydrzt
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 15 Jul 1988
Alistair Cooke reflects on protection rackets in 1930s Manhattan, the meaning of indict and remand, and the purpose and history of the US Grand Jury.